see also: Christ

The Catholic church - especially the papal ceremonies, symbols and instruments are veiled sun worship.


The circular Catholic host is sun symbology, especially when set in the Monstrance.

A monstrance is usually a gold frame with rays of the sun emitting all around a circular window containing the host.  Some monstrance have the letters SFS or IHS.


From WordNet (r) 2.0 : monstrance:
       n 1: proof by a process of argument or a series of proposition
            proving an asserted conclusion [syn: demonstration]
       2: (Roman Catholic Church) a vessel (usually of gold or silver)
          in which the consecrated Host is exposed for adoration


